ğŸ“¦ HTML Data Attributes

Used to store **custom data** in HTML elements.

```html
<button data-user-id="101">Click</button>
```

ğŸ“Œ Accessed using JavaScript
ğŸ“Œ Keeps HTML clean and flexible

---

ğŸ§± iframe (Embedding Content)

Used to embed **external content** like maps, videos, websites.

```html
<iframe src="https://example.com" width="400" height="300"></iframe>
```

ğŸ“Œ Common uses:

* YouTube videos
* Google Maps
* External pages

---

ğŸ¥ Advanced Multimedia

### Video with Controls & Poster

```html
<video controls width="400" poster="thumbnail.jpg">
  <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
```

Audio with Loop

```html
<audio controls loop>
  <source src="audio.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
</audio>
```

---

ğŸ“ Meta Tags (SEO & Performance)

Meta tags go inside `<head>`.

```html
<meta name="description" content="HTML Advanced Notes">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

ğŸ“Œ Important for:

* SEO
* Mobile responsiveness
* Performance

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  HTML Accessibility (A11Y)

### Accessibility Best Practices

* Use semantic tags
* Always use `alt` for images
* Use `<label>` with `<input>`
* Proper heading order (`h1` â†’ `h6`)

```html
<label for="name">Name</label>
<input id="name" type="text">
```

